    uint64_t x = rng_state;
    x ^= x << 13;
    x ^= x >> 7;
    x ^= x << 17;
    rng_state = x;
    return x;
}
```

This implementation uses a global variable `rng_state` to store the random number generator's internal state. The `xorshift64` function takes no arguments and returns a 64-bit unsigned integer.

